title: For Sale:  BUMP FIRE STOCK
postcontent:
Bump Fire Buttstock is the latest iteration of the company's groundbreaking SSAR-15 OGR Original Bump Fire Stock, incorporating the same performance, reliability, and superior craftsmanship of the OGR with a new look designed to appear similar to many of today's popular, modern battle rifle stocks. The SSAR-15 SBS allows the shooter to safely bump fire their AR-15 from the shoulder, effectively and legally simulating fully automatic fire, and allowing for an unprecedented measure of control that is severely lacking when attempting to bump fire a rifle in the traditional, "from-the-hip" manner. 

 The SSAR-15 features a shelf that positions the shooter's index finger in a fixed position in front of the rifle's trigger. To fire, the upper receiver is moved forward with the support hand pushing on the forend, thereby bringing the trigger to the shooter's finger and discharging a round. The rifle's recoil causes the upper receiver to move rearward, allowing the trigger mechanism to reset. When the right amount of constant forward pressure is applied, the rifle will continue to fire as the trigger is brought forward and depressed by the shooter's stationary index finger, causing the gun to Bump Fire. With a little practice, the shooter will be capable of delivering accurate single shots, bursts, or even full magazine dumps on demand using the SSAR-15. 

 The SSAR-15 is designed for installation onto any Mil-Spec Diameter AR-15 Collapsible Stock Receiver Extension Buffer Tube. Installation involves removing the factory pistol grip, replacing it with the included Interface Block, and sliding the SSAR-15 onto the buffer tube. No permanent modifications or gunsmithing required! Each SSAR-15 assembly includes the SBS Buttstock, an Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions, BATFE Approval Letter and Lifetime Factory Warranty. Made in the USA. 

Technical Information: • Model: SSAR-15 SBS
• Stock Material: Reinforced High Strength Polymer 
• Length of Pull: 13" 
• Compatibility: AR-15 with Mil-Spec Diameter Collapsible Stock Buffer Tube 
• Includes: SSAR-15 SBS Stock, Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions, BATFE Approval Letter

title: For Sale:  1940 M38 Russian Mosin Nagant carbine
postcontent:
I picked this up the other day with the delusion i'd be able to keep it in my collection for a while, but we got the house we have been wanting so it has to go to help with the moving costs.

It's a solid shooter grade rifle. made in 1940, Non matching serial numbers. The M38 is the same rifle as the M44 and Type 53 in every respect save it never had a side folding bayonet. These were generally issued to rear echelon troops with little need for a bayonet.

This is a second year of production rifle. This one is not as much a collector (very little interest there for a mutt like this) but as a general shooter, hunter. base for a custom build, it's the place to be. Condition is fair to good. the bore is weak, but still serviceable. (If you want to replace it for an accurized target shooter or whatever, i can put you on a site that has original and custom bull barrels for sale) Someone has replaced the rear sight blade with a mojo peep style. No import stamps.

It is what it is, a solid shooter that you can go several directions with.

Pick up at my place in camdenton/linn creek

No trades
$225 Firm
